A vintage-style illustration of an old wooden filing cabinet with multiple drawers pulled open at different angles, revealing cascading paper documents organized into colorful tabbed categories. The papers flow and transform into an intricate origami-like structure, folding and unfolding in mid-air. A magnifying glass hovers nearby, its lens creating prismatic light refractions across the organized chaos. The scene is rendered in warm sepia tones with touches of faded teal and burgundy, featuring subtle paper texture throughout. The composition suggests both the complexity and elegance of bringing order to nested, hierarchical information systems. Dust motes float in streams of golden afternoon light coming from an unseen window.
